                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A14/462½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>341. Your despatch No. 7615 of June 21, 1927. Please ascertain discreetly and
                    telegraph results of proposed conference of three Powers with Abyssinia and
                    present status of arms traffic control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
